{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016fUg8mpHQBQGP8DeqtiqML","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working correctly. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Problem**: The StatefulSet had 5 replicas (should be 3), no probes configured, and the `health-user` for probe authentication didn't exist in MongoDB.\n\n**Fix applied**:\n\n1. **Created `health-user`** in MongoDB with `clusterMonitor` role — this is the credential used by probes.\n\n2. **Reconfigured the replica set** from 5 to 3 members (removed members _id=3 and _id=4 one at a time, stepping down the primary in between).\n\n3. **Scaled the StatefulSet** from 5 to 3 replicas.\n\n4. **Added tuned probes** to the StatefulSet:\n   - **Liveness**: `mongosh --eval \"db.adminCommand({ping:1})\"` via health-user — verifies MongoDB is alive and auth works\n   - **Readiness**: checks `db.hello()` for `isWritablePrimary` or `secondary` — marks the pod ready only when it's in an active RS state (PRIMARY or SECONDARY)\n   - Both use `initialDelaySeconds: 30`, `timeoutSeconds: 10`, `failureThreshold: 6` to handle MongoDB's startup time without premature kills\n\n**Final state**: 3 pods all `1/1 Ready`, replica set has 1 PRIMARY (replica-1) and 2 SECONDARY members."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":761,"cache_read_input_tokens":54054,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":761},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d89a3b2f-22dc-4307-b938-39e1b9dfa7af","uuid":"04b0d1a9-4ea7-48fe-8e32-6634ccb0f2ef","request_id":"req_011CccLJzPMFJDthDik4kTSU"}
